snippet.textDisplay: Both wanted the other to fight a certain way. But they both knew that and didn't take each others bait. Romero's plan was simply wait for adesanya to step in range and counter. It worked a few times (that left tho) but he never followed up maybe to conserve energy. Adesanya won because he adjusted to the situation earlier. Stepping in range enough to strike and gliding out to avoid the bombs. Also izzy kept getting easy  picks to the leg. Romero adjusted later on the 5th by attacking/pushing more, even countering izzys low kicks by catching them and following up with a bomb up top but it wasnt enough. He adjusted too late in the match and he still had alot left in his gas tank at the end. He should have let his hands go in the 4th.

snippet.textDisplay:
Costa will give Adesanya big problems because he will come forward and force a tough fight. Adesanya is the type of fighter that wants space to fight, Costa will likely rob him of that space. Or at least he should, because that minimizes Adesanya’s reach advantage. Adesanya thrives when he can be flashy. Costa needs to make it a close in brawl and likely will. The issue will be can Costa keep up the pace for 5 rounds if needed?
That’s why Gastelum was his hardest fight so far. He can forward more then others. I think Costa could take it if he doesn’t hold back and makes it a brawl like he did Romero! That’s why Dana says this will be a different fight, because Costa will come forward!

snippet.textDisplay:
Izzy was the champ, the budding superstar, the new dazzling talent you need to see. The one considered one of the best strikers and one the best fighters in the UFC. He's the one - Izzy - who has to entertain and impress every time he enters the octagon to build his brand in the US and prove the hype is real. The expectations, the pressure were on him, not on a 43 year old fighter who has two years left in this sport, can't speak English and isn't destined to be a draw in the future.

Izzy wanted to fight Yoel, "the boogeyman of the division", talked all that smack before the fight, about how he wanted to be the first man to stop Yoel "properly" and make him "crumble like the twin towers". He wanted to make a statement. But de did none of that. Not only his performance wasn't good at all, it was incredibly boring, had fans leaving the arena during the fight, booing the lack of action and booing him specifically during his post-fight speech while Romero got cheered.
